sentences: Sons of Elvis was an alternative rock group active in the early 1990s, best known for their hit single, "Formaldehyde".
Priority Records then picked up the group and released the Mrs. White disc (consisting mainly of tracks from Glodean) before re-releasing Glodean in 1995.
Glodean peaked at No. 23 on Billboard's Top Heatseekers chart in 1995.
